In this op-ed, Vice President Joe Biden and Dr. Jill Biden discuss the challenges that veterans face when transitioning from military to civilian life, particularly in finding employment. They emphasize the skills and abilities of the 9/11 generation of veterans and argue that employers should be competing to hire them. The Bidens highlight the efforts of the Obama Administration to create financial incentives for companies to hire veterans and provide them with the necessary education and training. They also mention the American Jobs Act and the Joining Forces initiative, which aim to encourage companies to hire veterans. The op-ed concludes with a call to support and hire veterans, emphasizing their leadership, talent, and courage in both military and civilian contexts.